Class Burger

java.lang.Object
com.example.project4.model.MenuItem
com.example.project4.model.Sandwich
com.example.project4.model.Burger
public class Burger extends Sandwich
Represents a burger, which is a type of sandwich with additional functionality for a double patty option and specific pricing logic based on patty count and add-ons.
Author:
Yakelin Melendez-Gonzalez, Nivedha Sundar

      public Burger(Bread bread, Protein protein, ArrayList<AddOns> addOns, int quantity, boolean doublePatty)
      Constructs a Burger object with specified bread, protein, add-ons, quantity, and double patty option.
      Parameters:
      bread - The type of bread for the burger.
      protein - The type of protein for the burger (e.g., beef, chicken).
      addOns - A list of add-ons for the burger (e.g., lettuce, tomato).
      quantity - The number of burgers.
      doublePatty - Whether the burger has a double patty or not.

      public double price()
      Calculates the price of the burger based on the base patty price, the double patty option, and the total cost of add-ons. The price is then multiplied by the quantity.
